==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cathartin
<hw>ca*thar"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>The bitter, purgative principle of senna. It is a glucoside with
the properties of a weak acid; -- called also <altname>cathartic
acid</altname>, and <altname>cathartina</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cathay</ent>⟦br⟧
